Kathryn Hopkins
Economics Correspondent
Published at 12:01AM, April 4 2013
Businesses need to change to attract the “grey pound” as the number of over-65s in Britain is set to surge by 4.5 million by 2030.
A new report by Capital Economics estimates that the spending power of this age group will jump by a staggering £40 billion in under two decades and warned firms that they could suffer if they fail to entice the growing grey market to part with their cash.
